1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:05,720
Modern psychology, 
which is descended from humanism,

2
00:00:06,488 --> 00:00:12,228
they’re trying to encourage people
to believe in themselves.

3
00:00:12,248 --> 00:00:15,851
[Being Humble—Go for It]

4
00:00:16,241 --> 00:00:24,521
So much so, that in the modern world 
people are aggressive, beyond assertive,

5
00:00:24,521 --> 00:00:33,131
they’ve gone beyond submissiveness, 
humility, being virtuous—

6
00:00:33,131 --> 00:00:39,287
admirable, desirable qualities—
to … in the Darwinian world,

7
00:00:39,287 --> 00:00:47,374
where only the strong survive
and survival of the fittest.

8
00:00:47,374 --> 00:00:51,303
We are being told, “We’ve got
to be assertive, aggressive, go for it

9
00:00:51,303 --> 00:00:54,492
because you’re number one.
you’re worth it.”

10
00:00:54,492 --> 00:00:59,877
All of this kind of things, 
which is the antithesis of spiritual culture.

11
00:00:59,877 --> 00:01:04,680
Because for the finite, 
any finite to think

12
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:12,160
that they are the Infinite, 
or by another name—God,

13
00:01:12,231 --> 00:01:19,411
is the ultimate folly or foolishness
to think that you are the Supreme Entity,

14
00:01:19,438 --> 00:01:22,628
that the Universe
revolves around you.

15
00:01:28,279 --> 00:01:37,577
Humility is the outcome
of the perceived presence

16
00:01:37,577 --> 00:01:44,807
or proximity of greatness.
It’s not a posing, a posture.

17
00:01:45,035 --> 00:01:50,255
An actor can act humble;
the director can tell the actor,

18
00:01:50,255 --> 00:01:57,052
“In this scene you’re very humble.” 
He can tell a super arrogant person—
 

19
00:01:57,052 --> 00:02:00,152
they may be super arrogant
in their normal life—

20
00:02:00,152 --> 00:02:02,442
“But in this scene 
you are very humble.”

21
00:02:03,012 --> 00:02:04,792
They may be totally insensitive—
 

22
00:02:04,792 --> 00:02:08,991
“You’re very moody, you’re crying, 
you’re feeling that …”

23
00:02:08,991 --> 00:02:13,684
So, we are not talking 
about an act or pose,

24
00:02:14,394 --> 00:02:18,074
being a poseur—
posing as being humble.

25
00:02:18,075 --> 00:02:23,475
But humility should come 
as a natural outcome 
 

26
00:02:23,475 --> 00:02:29,079
of being in proximity to greatness.
Just as if we are standing 
 

27
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:34,876
on the shore of an ocean—
automatically, as we’re looking
 

28
00:02:34,876 --> 00:02:37,928
towards the horizon, 
we see how vast the ocean is,

29
00:02:37,928 --> 00:02:42,258
automatically feelings of humility
may descend within us.

